Robert Youngjohns
Executive Vice President, Strategic Business Development














Robert Youngjohns is Executive Vice President, Strategic Business Development for Hewlett Packard Enterprise. In this role, Robert is responsible for partnering with other members of the leadership team to drive strategic customer and partner initiatives focused on growing key parts of the business.
Previously, Robert served as Executive Vice President and General Manager of the Software business within HPE. Prior to joining HP in 2012, Robert held the role of President of Microsoft North America, as well as President and Chief Executive Officer of Callidus Software, where he initiated the company’s transition from traditional enterprise software to SaaS (Software as a Service).
Robert holds a master’s degree with honors in Physics and Philosophy from Oriel College, Oxford University.














