Robert Youngjohns Sold 117185 shares of Hewlett-Packard Company (NYSE:HPQ) in an Insider Trade


05/28/2015  by OctaStaff 
			in Blue Chips, Insider News, Insider Sells $2m+ 












Share with your friendsYour NameYour EmailRecipient EmailEnter a MessageI read this article and found it very interesting, thought it might be interesting for you. The article is called Robert Youngjohns Sold 117185 shares of Hewlett-Packard Company (NYSE:HPQ) in an Insider Trade and is was published by Octafinance.com at http://www.octafinance.com/robert-youngjohns-sold-117185-shares-of-hewlett-packard-company-nysehpq-in-an-insider-trade/68291/.CaptchaSubmit
Robert Youngjohns Insider Sell Transaction
 Mr. Robert Youngjohns, the current EVP and GM – HP Software at Hewlett-Packard Company (NYSE:HPQ)  19.15 +0.21 1.11% has a few days ago been involved with a stock market trade of 117,185 shares of the computer and electronic product manufacturing’s company, valued at $33.4 per share. The total stocks unloaded with a value of of $3,908,225 U.S. Dollars. This is a major deal, and one that is unlikely to remain undiscovered, as it decreased his ownership of the company to 0.00% stock market capitalization, for a total of 18,770 shares. Published 28-05-2015, you can learn more about the deal by referring to the following public report here. 
Hewlett Packard Co Stock Rating, Sentiment and Fundamentals
 The twenty nine leading stock analysts who dissected the California-based Hewlett Packard Co’s financial future, indicated an earnings per share of $3.65 and a Price to Earnings ratio of 9.26. The expert analysts expect year over year earnings for each share growth rate of not more than 1.97%. It is difficult to make conclusions about Hewlett Packard Co’s future just from Robert Youngjohns’s sale because in this filing, the insider also revealed option transactions. In the form, it was reported that Robert exercised options for 117,185 shares with average price 19.0, worth 2.23 million.






