Hedge Funds Ownership
 Data gathered from SEC filings, show that 942 hedge funds owned shares of Hewlett Packard Co. The institutional ownership of Hewlett Packard Co’s stock in the last quarter is extremely high, at 76.49% of the shares outstanding. They decreased by 51.99 million the total shares they hold. As of that quarter these banks and hedge funds owned 1.39 billion shares. A total of 125 funds opened new positions in Hewlett Packard Co and 296 increased their holdings. There were 76 funds that closed their positions and 394 that reduced them. 
 Hewlett Packard Co is Top 10 in 47 of them. Some of them are: Cypress Capital Management Llc, Dodge & Cox, Edmp Inc., Goodhaven Capital Management Llc, Jupiter Asset Management Ltd, Kempner Capital Management Inc., Poplar Forest Capital Llc, Pzena Investment Management Llc, Seminole Management Co. Inc., Todd Asset Management Llc.
  Cypress Capital Management Llc is the most positive institutional investor on Hewlett Packard Co, with ownership of 454,450 shares as of Q4 2014 for 5.27% of the fund’s portfolio. Dodge & Cox is another positive investment manager owning 143.24 million shares of the company or 5.32% of their stocks portfolio. The stock is also 2.57% of the fund’s AUM. Edmp Inc. have 6.07% of their stock portfolio invested in the stock for 161,569 shares. Further, The Florida-based fund Goodhaven Capital Management Llc disclosed it had acquired a stake worth 12.86% of the fund’s stock portfolio in the company. The United Kingdom-based fund Jupiter Asset Management Ltd was also a notable believer in the California-based company, with ownership of 4.98 million shares. Hewlett Packard Co is 0.01% of the fund’s stock portfolio.
Hewlett-Packard Company NYSE:HPQ Company Profile

Hewlett-Packard Company is a global provider of products, technologies, software, solutions and services to individual consumers, small- and medium-sized businesses (SMBs) and large enterprises, including customers in the government, health and education sectors. The Company offers IT industry’s broadest portfolios of products and services that bring infrastructure, software, and services through innovation to enable its customers to create value and solve business problems. The Company designs its solutions to provide foundation, in the areas of security, cloud, mobility and big data, by leveraging the breadth of its offerings and the strengths and capabilities of its individual business units. The Company’s operations are organized into seven business segments: Personal Systems; Printing; the Enterprise Group; Enterprise Services; Software; HP Financial Services, and Corporate Investments.
Company Website: Hewlett-Packard Company
 Hewlett Packard Co was formed in Delaware on 1998-02-11. Today its market value is: $61.16 billion and it has 1.81 billion shares outstanding. This company has 302000 employees. Currently the company has 79.59% shareholders and the institutional ownership stands at 79.59%. The stock closed at $33.78 yesterday and it had average 2 days volume of 2094214 shares. It is down from the 30 days average shares volume of 2340848. Hewlett Packard Co has a 52weeks low of $31.00 and a one year high of $41.10. The current price is below the 200 days simple moving average. Hewlett Packard Co last issued its quarterly earnings information on 05/21/2015. The company reported 0.87 EPS for the quarter, above the consensus estimate of 0.86 by 0.01. The company had a revenue of 26.84 billion for 1/31/2015 and 28.41 billion for 10/31/2014. Therefore, the revenue was -1,567,000,000 down.
Robert Youngjohns is also Vice President of Sun Microsystems, Inc., director of Callidus Software Inc.
